Project Homepage

G.W. Leibniz: The Philosophy of Situation

Geometric Characteristic and other essays on analysis situs

Editor: Matthew McMillan
Translators: David Jekel, Matthew McMillan

Overview

This site shares work on a collection of translations of writings of G.W. Leibniz on his analysis situs. Most of these writings currently have no English edition.

Translations are based primarily on Gerhardt typescripts that are corrected by the Leibniz Archiv specifically for this project (and for eventual inclusion in the Akademie-Ausgabe). We also draw on typescripts published by Couturat, by Mugnai, by Echeverria, and by the Mathesis and Philiumm projects.

  • Part I of the volume features the Specimen Geometriae Luciferae and other essays on the philosophy of geometry and space, giving Leibnizs preliminary encyclopedia of the concepts of geometry.
  • Part II features the Characteristica Geometrica and other essays emphasizing aspects of logic, language, and calculus that have been somewhat neglected in English studies of analysis situs.

We hope this volume provides a useful source for Leibniz scholars, as well as a very readable book for English-speaking philosophers and historians of mathematics and computation.

New Texts in the History of Philosophy
British Society for the History of Philosophy
